Lucas Johnson

Bio

I’m a Ph.D. student at SUNY ESF studying carbon mapping and monitoring under Dr. Colin Beier. My work focuses on methods for leveraging open data to produce maps of forest structure at local scales relevant to management. I have a strong background in programming and computer science, and have been learning to couple these skills with statistical modeling and machine learning techniques to produce landscape-level insights. I enjoy the challenges that come with wrangling all kinds of spatial data using R, and python.

Education

SUNY College of Environmental Science & Forestry | Syracuse, NY

Ph.D. in Environmental Science | August 2019 - Present

Tufts University | Medford, MA

B.S. in Computer Science | August 2013 - May 2017

Experience

Research Assistant | SUNY ESF, CAFRI | August 2019 - Present

Data Engineer | Lightkeeper, LLC | August 2017 - July 2019
